Celebrities in the US and elsewhere have been left shocked following Donald Trump's victory in the US presidential elections. JOHANNESBURG - Hillary Clinton has had a lot of support from people of all walks of life - politicians, actors, comedians and singers.The news that Donald Trump is the new US president has now hit home and Clinton supporters are finding it hard to believe.Take a look at some of the reactions.Chris Evans, who has starred in The Avengers movies as Captain America has expressed disbelief:This is an embarrassing night for America. We&#39;ve let a hatemonger lead our great nation. We&#39;ve let a bully set our course. I&#39;m devastated.Katy Perry has encouraged people to not change who they are.Do not sit still. Do not weep. MOVE. We are not a nation that will let HATE lead us.Khloe Kardashian had a nail biting experience as the results were coming in earlier.It shouldn&#39;t be this close #ElectionNightTrevor Noah said it feels like a joke.This is like a sketch.In South Africa, Black Coffee was shocked.USA Fikile Mbalula, the Minister of Sports, said something that tweeps found ironic. America is like one big Orania now